 Oh, boy.

261
00:10:25,240 --> 00:10:26,540
 Henry, where are you going?

262
00:10:26,540 --> 00:10:27,540
 I'll be right back, Eleanor.

263
00:10:27,540 --> 00:10:29,880
 Just as soon as I get something straight now.

264
00:10:29,880 --> 00:10:31,300
 Homer, hey Homer.

265
00:10:31,300 --> 00:10:32,140
 - What, Henry?

266
00:10:32,140 --> 00:10:33,860
 - As long as you're waiting around for Agnes.

267
00:10:33,860 --> 00:10:36,100
 How would you like to earn 50 cents?

268
00:10:36,100 --> 00:10:38,680
 (upbeat music)

269
00:10:38,680 --> 00:10:47,520
 - Alice.

270
00:10:47,520 --> 00:10:50,380
 Alice, are you upstairs?

271
00:10:50,380 --> 00:10:51,820
 (phone ringing)

272
00:10:51,820 --> 00:10:52,660
 Alice.

273
00:10:55,020 --> 00:10:56,420
 Hello, Sam always speaking.

274
00:10:56,420 --> 00:10:58,320
 Sam, this is Alice.

275
00:10:58,320 --> 00:11:00,420
 What's that Alice? When did you leave the house?

276
00:11:00,420 --> 00:11:03,220
 Why, you're quite a while ago, dear.

277
00:11:03,220 --> 00:11:06,220
 And dear, I hate to bother you when I know you're reading your papers,

278
00:11:06,220 --> 00:11:09,020
 but I'm afraid you'll have to come over and get me.

279
00:11:09,020 --> 00:11:09,820
 Get you?

280
00:11:09,820 --> 00:11:13,120
 Yes, I have a flat tire.

281
00:11:13,120 --> 00:11:14,520
 You mean you took the car?

282
00:11:14,520 --> 00:11:16,620
 Oh, no, dear. I am.

283
00:11:16,620 --> 00:11:18,220
 Well, I took...

284
00:11:18,220 --> 00:11:19,020
 Well...

285
00:11:19,020 --> 00:11:19,820
 You what?

286
00:11:19,820 --> 00:11:21,820
 And nothing, Sam. Just forget it.

287
00:11:21,820 --> 00:11:22,920
 Goodbye, dear.

288
00:11:22,920 --> 00:11:24,920
 Dennis, what are you talking about?

289
00:11:24,920 --> 00:11:26,920
 Alice, where are you?

290
00:11:26,920 --> 00:11:38,920
 Hello, can you hear me, Mother?

291
00:11:38,920 --> 00:11:43,920
 Yes, Humma, and I'm sorry, but your father says he absolutely won't help you out.

292
00:11:43,920 --> 00:11:45,920
 But Mother doesn't he understand what's happened?

293
00:11:45,920 --> 00:11:50,920
 Henry gave me 50 cents, provided I go over to his house and get a delivery bicycle he has

294
00:11:50,920 --> 00:11:53,120
 and take it to McCall's drug store, see?

295
00:11:53,120 --> 00:11:53,960
 - Yes.

296
00:11:53,960 --> 00:11:55,480
 - And just after I took the 50 cents

297
00:11:55,480 --> 00:11:56,720
 and bought some punch with it,

298
00:11:56,720 --> 00:11:58,360
 who do you think showed up?

299
00:11:58,360 --> 00:11:59,200
 - Who?

300
00:11:59,200 --> 00:12:01,160
 - Agnes with a different dress on.

301
00:12:01,160 --> 00:12:04,200
 And before she'd even dash, she had to have some punch.

302
00:12:04,200 --> 00:12:06,440
 Boy, she went right through 20 cents.

303
00:12:06,440 --> 00:12:07,360
 (audience laughs)

304
00:12:07,360 --> 00:12:08,560
 And I wondered where the father

305
00:12:08,560 --> 00:12:10,840
 wouldn't be willing to deliver that bicycle for me.

306
00:12:10,840 --> 00:12:13,400
 Provided I'd give him part of next week's allowance.

307
00:12:13,400 --> 00:12:15,760
 - You're afraid Agnes will be hurt if you leave.

308
00:12:15,760 --> 00:12:17,680
 - Well sure, wouldn't you be?

309
00:12:17,680 --> 00:12:20,440
 - Well, do you know, I'll have a talk with your father.

310
00:12:20,440 --> 00:12:22,740
 Only he has his shoes off and you know what that means.

311
00:12:22,740 --> 00:12:24,740
 But mother, you know how to handle him.

312
00:12:24,740 --> 00:12:27,180
 She was all you have to do is talk to him the way you do

313
00:12:27,180 --> 00:12:29,180
 and you can get him into his shoes.

314
00:12:29,180 --> 00:12:30,180
 [LAUGHTER]

315
00:12:30,180 --> 00:12:31,620
 Don't worry.

316
00:12:31,620 --> 00:12:33,300
 You go on when you're dancing.

317
00:12:33,300 --> 00:12:35,300
 After all, you're only young one.

318
00:12:35,300 --> 00:12:37,300
 [MUSIC PLAYING]

319
00:12:37,300 --> 00:12:48,860
 Get over on your own side of the street.

320
00:12:48,860 --> 00:12:52,540
 Suppose you get over on your side, you big...

321
00:12:52,540 --> 00:12:57,180
 Alice, oh, could you set you on that machine?

322
00:12:57,180 --> 00:12:58,180
 Harriet!

323
00:12:58,180 --> 00:12:58,940
 Aah!

324
00:12:58,940 --> 00:13:00,220
 Look out, I'll run over you.

325
00:13:00,220 --> 00:13:02,180
 What's the matter, can't you stop?

326
00:13:02,180 --> 00:13:04,700
 Not the first time I back up my seat!

327
00:13:04,700 --> 00:13:09,300
 There.

328
00:13:09,300 --> 00:13:10,940
 Now help me off.

329
00:13:10,940 --> 00:13:14,580
 Alice, Colbridge, may I ask what you're doing?

330
00:13:14,580 --> 00:13:16,540
 Harriet, you're just the person I want to see.

331
00:13:16,540 --> 00:13:20,040
 Could you take this package of ice cream into the Allison's house here?

332
00:13:20,040 --> 00:13:21,740
 What are you doing?

333
00:13:21,740 --> 00:13:23,320
 Delivering packages.

334
00:13:23,320 --> 00:13:24,640
 Packages?

335
00:13:24,640 --> 00:13:25,740
 For the poor?

336
00:13:25,740 --> 00:13:27,940
 Harriet.

337
00:13:27,940 --> 00:13:33,040
 The Allysons are giving a party in there, and I have got their ice cream, and I haven't been invited.

338
00:13:33,040 --> 00:13:33,840
 And...

339
00:13:33,840 --> 00:13:35,740
 Well, so you'll just have to take it in for me.

340
00:13:35,740 --> 00:13:38,740
 But, Allison, I'm late for a bridge party over at the Anderson's.

341
00:13:38,740 --> 00:13:40,340
 But don't you understand?

342
00:13:40,340 --> 00:13:42,940
 Dress the way I am. I can't go into the Allysons.

343
00:13:42,940 --> 00:13:46,640
 Frankly, you're the canines and only think I'm trying to crash their party.

344
00:13:46,640 --> 00:13:53,340
 Now, Harriet, do you remember on your 13th birthday when you were too bashful to ask Bill Townsend to your party

345
00:13:53,340 --> 00:13:58,940
 and I did it for you and you swore you'd do anything in the world for me any time I asked you?

346
00:13:58,940 --> 00:14:00,240
 No.

347
00:14:00,240 --> 00:14:03,240
 Harriet, you did not?

348
00:14:03,240 --> 00:14:05,640
 Well, anyway, you're going right over by Maple Street.

349
00:14:05,640 --> 00:14:08,640
 Could you at least leave this bottle of course here at the 227?

350
00:14:08,640 --> 00:14:09,940
 Who is it important?

351
00:14:09,940 --> 00:14:10,940
 It's very important.

352
00:14:10,940 --> 00:14:13,500
 And you see, Mr. McCall just started a new drugstore,

353
00:14:13,500 --> 00:14:15,340
 and Henry's trying to help him out.

354
00:14:15,340 --> 00:14:16,940
 Well, all right.

355
00:14:16,940 --> 00:14:18,860
 And Alice, if you don't want to see the Alice's,

356
00:14:18,860 --> 00:14:21,260
 why don't you just leave the ice cream on the front porch,

357
00:14:21,260 --> 00:14:22,580
 ring the bell, and run?

358
00:14:22,580 --> 00:14:24,860
 Because there's $1.40 on it.

359
00:14:24,860 --> 00:14:27,900
 Oh, and there's $0.90 on the coalf syrup.

360
00:14:27,900 --> 00:14:30,220
 And don't lose it in the bridge game.

361
00:14:30,220 --> 00:14:33,660
 [MUSIC PLAYING]

362
00:14:33,660 --> 00:14:36,240
 (upbeat music)

363
00:14:36,240 --> 00:14:46,500
 - Hello, my car's pharmacy.

364
00:14:46,500 --> 00:14:49,320
 - Oh, lady, I sent that call, sir,

365
00:14:49,320 --> 00:14:50,780
 about nearly 40 minutes ago.

366
00:14:50,780 --> 00:14:52,720
 I've got a new delivery girl, see?

367
00:14:52,720 --> 00:14:54,080
 And she is.

368
00:14:54,080 --> 00:14:55,440
 - What?

369
00:14:55,440 --> 00:14:56,760
 What's that?

370
00:14:56,760 --> 00:14:59,400
 - Oh, yes, well, when the girl gets there,

371
00:14:59,400 --> 00:15:01,680
 you give her the other bottle you want refill,

372
00:15:01,680 --> 00:15:03,940
 and tell her to bring it back here.

373
00:15:03,940 --> 00:15:04,880
 (laughs)

374
00:15:04,880 --> 00:15:07,040
 Forget it, no trouble at all.

375
00:15:07,040 --> 00:15:08,380
 Come by.

376
00:15:08,380 --> 00:15:09,220
 - Good evening.

377
00:15:09,220 --> 00:15:10,880
 - Yo, hey, hey, yes, good evening,

378
00:15:10,880 --> 00:15:12,080
 something I can do for you.

379
00:15:12,080 --> 00:15:13,980
 - Well, could you tell me,

380
00:15:13,980 --> 00:15:16,180
 have you seen my wife this evening?

381
00:15:16,180 --> 00:15:17,520
 - Your wife.

382
00:15:17,520 --> 00:15:19,920
 - Isn't this where Henry Aldrich works?

383
00:15:19,920 --> 00:15:22,320
 - This is where he's supposed to work.

384
00:15:22,320 --> 00:15:23,300
 - Well, what I mean is,

385
00:15:23,300 --> 00:15:25,800
 did my wife bring a bicycle down here?

386
00:15:25,800 --> 00:15:28,200
 - Oh, you, Henry's brother-in-law, how do you do?

387
00:15:28,200 --> 00:15:29,600
 (audience laughs)

388
00:15:29,600 --> 00:15:30,440
 - I beg your pardon?

389
00:15:30,440 --> 00:15:33,000
 I don't want to complain about your wife, sir,

390
00:15:33,000 --> 00:15:35,840
 but I sent her out with some packages nearly an hour ago.

391
00:15:35,840 --> 00:15:36,560
 Some packages?

392
00:15:36,560 --> 00:15:38,400
 And I've got some more for her to take out,

393
00:15:38,400 --> 00:15:40,360
 and she hasn't come back yet.

394
00:15:40,360 --> 00:15:42,600
 You mean, Alice, by wife?

395
00:15:42,600 --> 00:15:45,160
 And what I want to know is what you're

396
00:15:45,160 --> 00:15:46,760
 going to do about it.

397
00:15:46,760 --> 00:15:48,240
 What I'm going to do about it--

398
00:15:48,240 --> 00:15:50,680
 I thought your family was the kind that could be relied on.

399
00:15:50,680 --> 00:15:52,480
 We are the kind that can be relied on.

400
00:15:52,480 --> 00:15:54,000
 That's why we're helping you out.

401
00:15:54,000 --> 00:15:55,080
 What do you mean by we?

402
00:15:55,080 --> 00:15:57,520
 I haven't seen you do anything yet.

403
00:15:57,520 --> 00:15:58,200
 What, sir?

404
00:15:58,200 --> 00:15:59,600
 Listen, I'm going out and delivering

405
00:15:59,600 --> 00:16:00,940
 a couple of these orders myself.

406
00:16:00,940 --> 00:16:02,680
 You stay here and take care of the store.

407
00:16:02,680 --> 00:16:03,520
 - What's that?

408
00:16:03,520 --> 00:16:05,880
 - And if there's anything you can't find just that.

409
00:16:05,880 --> 00:16:08,340
 - That's, that's cool.

410
00:16:08,340 --> 00:16:10,920
 (upbeat music)

411
00:16:10,920 --> 00:16:19,840
 - Eleanor, do you mind if I suggest something?

412
00:16:19,840 --> 00:16:20,680
 - What Henry?

413
00:16:20,680 --> 00:16:22,440
 - Well let's hit this next dance out.

414
00:16:22,440 --> 00:16:23,280
 - All right.

415
00:16:23,280 --> 00:16:24,120
 - As a matter of fact,

416
00:16:24,120 --> 00:16:25,320
 let's go out in the porch and get some air.

417
00:16:25,320 --> 00:16:26,160
 - All right.

418
00:16:26,160 --> 00:16:29,320
 - Boy, do I feel good.

419
00:16:29,320 --> 00:16:32,480
 Ever since I got home we're lined up to take that bicycle back for me.

420
00:16:32,480 --> 00:16:34,560
 It just goes to show.

421
00:16:34,560 --> 00:16:36,800
 What goes to show?

422
00:16:36,800 --> 00:16:40,040
 I mean, you've got a job, see, and you're conscientious about it.

423
00:16:40,040 --> 00:16:40,800
 It pays.

424
00:16:40,800 --> 00:16:43,120
 Now I was just talking to Mr. Scott a few minutes ago

425
00:16:43,120 --> 00:16:45,560
 and he asked me whether I wouldn't like a job working for him.

426
00:16:45,560 --> 00:16:46,520
 Really?

427
00:16:46,520 --> 00:16:48,720
 Provided I can give him some good references.

428
00:16:48,720 --> 00:16:50,440
 Gee, I wouldn't hesitate a minute,

429
00:16:50,440 --> 00:16:52,120
 ask you Mr. McCall for one.

430
00:16:52,120 --> 00:16:54,320
 Henry, isn't that Agnes Lawson?

431
00:16:54,320 --> 00:16:55,000
 Where?

432
00:16:55,000 --> 00:16:56,800
 At the end of the porch there in the moonlight.

433
00:16:57,920 --> 00:17:00,520
 You know who you suppose that boy is.

434
00:17:00,520 --> 00:17:02,180
 Hey, let's walk down and see.

435
00:17:02,180 --> 00:17:03,360
 Wait until I tell Homer.

436
00:17:03,360 --> 00:17:06,120
 Just wait until I tell Homer.

437
00:17:06,120 --> 00:17:08,920
 Now listen, Hannah, you keep away from here.

438
00:17:08,920 --> 00:17:09,920
 Homer, is that you?

439
00:17:09,920 --> 00:17:10,600
 Come on, Max.

440
00:17:10,600 --> 00:17:11,680
 Let's get away from her.

441
00:17:11,680 --> 00:17:13,840
 Yeah, but then Homer, how about my bicycle?

442
00:17:13,840 --> 00:17:16,640
 And don't you realize my whole reputation's at stake?

443
00:17:16,640 --> 00:17:18,640
 [MUSIC PLAYING]

444
00:17:18,640 --> 00:17:20,640
 [APPLAUSE]

