00:18:50,640 --> 00:18:53,640
 Because she's decided her son is young only once,

461
00:18:53,640 --> 00:18:56,640
 Mrs. Aldridge has consented to run an errand for Henry

462
00:18:56,640 --> 00:18:59,640
 in order that he may go to the country club dance.

463
00:18:59,640 --> 00:19:02,140
 The scene opens in the Aldrich front hall.

464
00:19:02,140 --> 00:19:04,340
 Homer Brown's father is on the phone.

465
00:19:04,340 --> 00:19:06,640
 Hello, hello, hello.

466
00:19:06,640 --> 00:19:08,640
 Hello, Mrs. Brown speaking.

467
00:19:08,640 --> 00:19:09,640
 Elizabeth, this is Will.

468
00:19:09,640 --> 00:19:10,640
 Who?

469
00:19:10,640 --> 00:19:11,640
 Will, your husband.

470
00:19:11,640 --> 00:19:14,140
 I can't find that bicycle of Henry's.

471
00:19:14,140 --> 00:19:15,640
 Oh, did you look all over there, your aunt?

472
00:19:15,640 --> 00:19:19,140
 I walked into every tree out there and there's still no sign of it.

473
00:19:19,140 --> 00:19:21,140
 Well, where are you now?

474
00:19:21,140 --> 00:19:22,640
 I'm in the Aldrich front hall.

475
00:19:22,640 --> 00:19:26,140
 And Elizabeth, I'm in my house slippers and I'm standing in water.

476
00:19:26,140 --> 00:19:27,140
 In water?

477
00:19:27,140 --> 00:19:31,140
 Well, I can't be responsible if they aren't more careful where they put their faces of flowers.

478
00:19:31,140 --> 00:19:33,140
 [audience laughter]

479
00:19:33,140 --> 00:19:35,140
 Well, me, you just got to find that bicycle.

480
00:19:35,140 --> 00:19:39,140
 Always says Henry was very much concerned about it being taken back.

481
00:19:39,140 --> 00:19:43,140
 And he won't enjoy the dance one bit if he knows who fallen down on him.

482
00:19:43,140 --> 00:19:45,140
 Well, I'll give him ten more minutes, and then I quit. Goodbye.

483
00:19:45,140 --> 00:19:46,140
 Bye.

484
00:19:46,140 --> 00:19:47,140
 [door opens]

485
00:19:47,140 --> 00:19:48,140
 [door opens]

486
00:19:48,140 --> 00:19:49,140
 [door opens]

487
00:19:49,140 --> 00:19:50,140
 [door opens]

488
00:19:50,140 --> 00:19:51,140
 [door opens]

489
00:19:51,140 --> 00:19:52,140
 [door opens]

490
00:19:52,140 --> 00:19:54,140
 Hold your heart here!

491
00:19:54,140 --> 00:19:55,140
 [door opens]

492
00:19:55,140 --> 00:19:56,140
 Hello.

493
00:19:56,140 --> 00:19:58,940
 - And what was this you, Father? - Homer, where are you?

494
00:19:58,940 --> 00:20:02,340
 - This isn't Homer, it's Henry. - Oh, it is. Well, there's Mr. Brown.

495
00:20:02,340 --> 00:20:05,940
 Mr. Brown, she was hot. I get the wrong number. Goodbye, Father.

496
00:20:05,940 --> 00:20:08,340
 - I mean, goodbye. - Oh, wait a minute. Wait a minute. Where's your bicycle?

497
00:20:08,340 --> 00:20:10,340
 Hello? Hello?

498
00:20:10,340 --> 00:20:24,740
 Excuse me, but could you give me some information?

499
00:20:24,740 --> 00:20:26,140
 What is it you'd like to know, lady?

500
00:20:26,140 --> 00:20:30,240
 Well, have you any idea where number 227 Maple Street would be?

501
00:20:30,240 --> 00:20:32,440
 Let's see now. Isn't it this house right here?

502
00:20:32,440 --> 00:20:35,540
 No, I was just in there and they haven't had a cold all year.

503
00:20:35,540 --> 00:20:36,640
 What's that?

504
00:20:36,640 --> 00:20:42,740
 227 Maple Street ordered this cough syrup and I'd like to get rid of it so I can go to a bridge party.

505
00:20:42,740 --> 00:20:43,940
 How about the house next door?

506
00:20:43,940 --> 00:20:47,840
 Oh, I tried that one too. They said they don't think there is any 227.

507
00:20:47,840 --> 00:20:49,240
 Let's see the address on your pack.

508
00:20:49,240 --> 00:20:50,240
 Here you are.

509
00:20:50,240 --> 00:20:52,140
 That's 227, all right.

510
00:20:52,140 --> 00:20:53,840
 Or 277.

511
00:20:53,840 --> 00:20:56,440
 - Is what? - And that certainly says maple.

512
00:20:56,440 --> 00:20:57,480
 Or is it marble?

513
00:20:57,480 --> 00:20:59,040
 Marble Street!

514
00:20:59,040 --> 00:21:01,640
 Don't get discouraged, lady. You're on the right track.

515
00:21:01,640 --> 00:21:13,720
 Now then, I'm sorry to keep you waiting, lady.

516
00:21:13,720 --> 00:21:15,280
 Is there something I can do for you?

517
00:21:15,280 --> 00:21:17,720
 Yes, sir. I'd like a chocolate swab.

518
00:21:17,720 --> 00:21:22,040
 A chocolate swab?

519
00:21:22,040 --> 00:21:24,280
 - Prostance. - Oh.

520
00:21:24,280 --> 00:21:25,800
 That's something to drink, isn't it?

