00:21:25,800 --> 00:21:29,440
 - Certainly is. It's made with chocolate syrup, milk, and ice cream.

522
00:21:29,440 --> 00:21:33,400
 - Yes, and that's all? - Yes, and then you put in that mixer.

523
00:21:33,400 --> 00:21:35,240
 - Here's what that sounds easy, enough.

524
00:21:35,240 --> 00:21:37,800
 Now then, lady, we'll get a glass.

525
00:21:37,800 --> 00:21:41,560
 Ah, here we are. - Oh, isn't that a Sunday dish?

526
00:21:41,560 --> 00:21:44,800
 - Oh, I see. You want a big drink? - That's right.

527
00:21:44,800 --> 00:21:48,480
 - Well, now, here, how's this size?

528
00:21:48,480 --> 00:21:51,120
 - Oh, my goodness. Do I get one that thick?

529
00:21:51,120 --> 00:21:52,880
 I think this is a drinking glass.

530
00:21:52,880 --> 00:21:55,120
 Couldn't be just an ornament, good, eh?

531
00:21:55,120 --> 00:21:56,600
 [LAUGHTER]

532
00:21:56,600 --> 00:21:57,520
 Now then, let's see.

533
00:21:57,520 --> 00:22:01,080
 I guess the logical thing would be to start with the chocolate.

534
00:22:01,080 --> 00:22:02,880
 Chocolate.

535
00:22:02,880 --> 00:22:05,040
 Chocolate.

536
00:22:05,040 --> 00:22:06,600
 You would miss it in strawberry, would you?

537
00:22:06,600 --> 00:22:08,160
 No, I don't.

538
00:22:08,160 --> 00:22:10,120
 I got strawberry right here.

539
00:22:10,120 --> 00:22:11,520
 A lemon?

540
00:22:11,520 --> 00:22:12,880
 That's parilla.

541
00:22:12,880 --> 00:22:15,880
 Maybe they keep the chocolate in one of these bowls.

542
00:22:15,880 --> 00:22:18,200
 No, that's the cherries.

543
00:22:18,200 --> 00:22:20,080
 Don't you like to have me throw a cherry in?

544
00:22:20,080 --> 00:22:22,640
 No, thank you. How about that other bowl?

545
00:22:22,640 --> 00:22:23,540
 This one?

546
00:22:23,540 --> 00:22:26,000
 Yes, that's a good one.

547
00:22:26,000 --> 00:22:30,320
 Well, I never saw anything like that before. It's sort of a lather.

548
00:22:30,320 --> 00:22:32,680
 Isn't that whipped cream?

549
00:22:32,680 --> 00:22:39,320
 Oh, so it is. It's been a long time since I've seen any whipped cream.

550
00:22:39,320 --> 00:22:42,720
 We're both wrong. It's mayonnaise.

551
00:22:42,720 --> 00:22:43,920
 That chocolate right here.

552
00:22:43,920 --> 00:22:46,880
 Oh, yes. Good for you, lady.

553
00:22:46,880 --> 00:22:49,880
 Well, here we go.

554
00:22:49,880 --> 00:22:52,140
 (barking)

555
00:22:52,140 --> 00:22:56,680
 - My goodness, this is not quite a lot of chocolate.

556
00:22:56,680 --> 00:22:58,880
 Are you gonna have room for the milk?

557
00:22:58,880 --> 00:23:00,600
 - And if we don't, we'll get another glass

558
00:23:00,600 --> 00:23:01,920
 and I'll drink part of it.

559
00:23:01,920 --> 00:23:03,160
 (audience laughing)

560
00:23:03,160 --> 00:23:05,640
 - Have you ever done this before?

561
00:23:05,640 --> 00:23:08,400
 - Not as a general rule.

562
00:23:08,400 --> 00:23:10,000
 Actually, I'm a lawyer.

563
00:23:10,000 --> 00:23:13,000
 - Oh, and you have to take this job night.

564
00:23:13,000 --> 00:23:15,880
 (audience laughing)

565
00:23:15,880 --> 00:23:17,800
 - Well, I have to take it tonight, anyhow.

566
00:23:17,800 --> 00:23:18,920
 Now then, let's see.

567
00:23:18,920 --> 00:23:20,000
 Here's the ice cream.

568
00:23:20,000 --> 00:23:22,400
 I wonder what they take it out with.

569
00:23:22,400 --> 00:23:23,840
 Wasn't there a scoop?

570
00:23:23,840 --> 00:23:27,200
 No, and I certainly don't want to use my hand.

571
00:23:27,200 --> 00:23:28,840
 My goodness, no.

572
00:23:28,840 --> 00:23:30,160
 Oh, here's the scoop right here.

573
00:23:30,160 --> 00:23:31,840
 Is that vanilla?

574
00:23:31,840 --> 00:23:32,720
 Oh, yes.

575
00:23:32,720 --> 00:23:35,840
 You can't fool me on vanilla.

576
00:23:35,840 --> 00:23:39,760
 Well, the ice cream won't come out of the scoop.

577
00:23:39,760 --> 00:23:42,000
 Well, all you have to do is squeeze that little jigger

578
00:23:42,000 --> 00:23:43,200
 and it drops right out.

579
00:23:43,200 --> 00:23:45,440
 Yes, I realize that.

580
00:23:45,440 --> 00:23:51,120
 But for some reason, for some reason, would you excuse me a minute

581
00:23:51,120 --> 00:23:54,280
 while I go out and back and see whether I can find a screwdriver?

582
00:23:54,280 --> 00:23:56,760
 [MUSIC PLAYING]

583
00:23:56,760 --> 00:23:59,760
 [MUSIC PLAYING]

584
00:23:59,760 --> 00:24:08,320
 Good evening.

585
00:24:08,320 --> 00:24:09,000
 Good evening.

586
00:24:09,000 --> 00:24:10,600
 Are you Mrs. Allison's maid?

587
00:24:10,600 --> 00:24:11,920
 I am.

588
00:24:11,920 --> 00:24:13,960
 Don't tell me that's our ice cream.

589
00:24:13,960 --> 00:24:14,840
 I'm afraid it is.

590
00:24:14,840 --> 00:24:16,340
 I was a little delayed on the way.

591
00:24:16,340 --> 00:24:17,600
 You were delayed?

592
00:24:17,600 --> 00:24:19,560
 Well, isn't that you I saw standing right out

593
00:24:19,560 --> 00:24:21,920
 in front of the house for the last 15 minutes?

594
00:24:21,920 --> 00:24:22,680
 Yes.

595
00:24:22,680 --> 00:24:25,560
 I was trying to get some boy to--

596
00:24:25,560 --> 00:24:26,640
 that is, I'm sorry.

597
00:24:26,640 --> 00:24:28,360
 But here's your ice cream if you don't want it,

598
00:24:28,360 --> 00:24:29,240
 you don't have to take it.

599
00:24:29,240 --> 00:24:30,240
 Thank you.

600
00:24:30,240 --> 00:24:32,040
 And there's $1.40 due on it.

601
00:24:32,040 --> 00:24:33,040
 All right.

602
00:24:33,040 --> 00:24:34,440
 Now wait right out there.

603
00:24:34,440 --> 00:24:37,280
 That's just what I intend to do.

604
00:24:37,280 --> 00:24:38,040
 Oh, Amy.

605
00:24:38,040 --> 00:24:38,960
 Yes, Mrs. Dallas.

606
00:24:38,960 --> 00:24:39,960
 And he's finally here.

607
00:24:39,960 --> 00:24:42,720
 And they want to collect $1.40.

608
00:24:42,720 --> 00:24:43,760
 All right.

609
00:24:43,760 --> 00:24:45,600
 Tell a boy I'll be right out and pay him.

610
00:24:45,600 --> 00:24:47,160
 It isn't a boy, it's a girl.

611
00:24:47,160 --> 00:24:47,960
 A girl?

612
00:24:47,960 --> 00:24:49,600
 Yes, ma'am.

613
00:24:49,600 --> 00:24:53,140
 Now then, young woman, here's your $1.40 and $0.10

614
00:24:53,140 --> 00:24:54,080
 for yourself.

615
00:24:54,080 --> 00:24:55,760
 Although you've been so long getting here,

616
00:24:55,760 --> 00:24:57,680
 you certainly don't--

617
00:24:57,680 --> 00:25:00,680
 Oh, my goodness, is that you, Mrs. Aldrich?

618
00:25:00,680 --> 00:25:02,560
 No, oh, yes, yes.

619
00:25:02,560 --> 00:25:03,960
 Good evening, Mrs. Allison.

620
00:25:03,960 --> 00:25:06,680
 Where's the young woman I'm supposed to give this to?

621
00:25:06,680 --> 00:25:07,600
 The young woman?

622
00:25:07,600 --> 00:25:09,120
 The one who brought the ice cream.

623
00:25:09,120 --> 00:25:09,960
 What did she do?

624
00:25:09,960 --> 00:25:11,440
 Going back to the store?

625
00:25:11,440 --> 00:25:13,840
 Well, I... Well, yes, yes.

626
00:25:13,840 --> 00:25:14,960
 Yes, I guess you must have.

627
00:25:14,960 --> 00:25:17,080
 I'm so glad you decided to come.

628
00:25:17,080 --> 00:25:18,440
 Where's Mr. Aldridge?

629
00:25:18,440 --> 00:25:19,280
 Well, come in.

630
00:25:19,280 --> 00:25:20,920
 Oh, no, I couldn't think of coming in.

631
00:25:20,920 --> 00:25:22,840
 Why not? We'd love to have you.

632
00:25:22,840 --> 00:25:24,760
 You're just in time for ice cream.

633
00:25:24,760 --> 00:25:25,960
 No, thanks, Mrs. Allison.

634
00:25:25,960 --> 00:25:28,560
 As a matter of fact, I don't know why I came over at all.

635
00:25:28,560 --> 00:25:30,280
 Was there something you wanted, dear?

636
00:25:30,280 --> 00:25:32,080
 Oh, no, no, just forget the whole thing.

637
00:25:32,080 --> 00:25:32,920
 Goodbye.

638
00:25:32,920 --> 00:25:33,760
 Goodbye.

639
00:25:33,760 --> 00:25:36,600
 (loud clattering)

640
00:25:36,600 --> 00:25:37,600
 My goodness.

641
00:25:37,600 --> 00:25:39,360
 Did you hurt yourself, Mrs. Aldridge?

642
00:25:39,360 --> 00:25:41,400
 No, no, I just fell over my bicycle.

643
00:25:41,400 --> 00:25:44,400
 [MUSIC PLAYING]

644
00:25:44,400 --> 00:25:53,120
 Say, isn't anybody in charge of this store?

645
00:25:53,120 --> 00:25:55,040
 Of course, just went around and back again.

646
00:25:55,040 --> 00:25:56,000
 Oh, yeah?

647
00:25:56,000 --> 00:25:57,440
 He's been mixing in your chocolate

648
00:25:57,440 --> 00:25:59,480
 frosted for the last half hour.

649
00:25:59,480 --> 00:26:00,920
 You ran into the little trouble.

650
00:26:00,920 --> 00:26:01,760
 Oh.

651
00:26:01,760 --> 00:26:03,160
 Mr. McColl, hello there.

652
00:26:03,160 --> 00:26:04,240
 I'll be right out.

653
00:26:04,240 --> 00:26:05,080
 Only half a minute.

654
00:26:05,080 --> 00:26:06,400
 I've got to get back home.

655
00:26:06,400 --> 00:26:07,800
 Now, then, what can I do for you?

656
00:26:07,800 --> 00:26:09,000
 But here's what I want to ask.

657
00:26:09,000 --> 00:26:10,640
 That bicycle.

658
00:26:10,640 --> 00:26:12,320
 Sam Ulrich.

659
00:26:12,320 --> 00:26:13,360
 Hello, well, Brown.

660
00:26:13,360 --> 00:26:14,760
 What are you doing in that apron?

661
00:26:14,760 --> 00:26:18,160
 Why, Sam, I can't find Henry's bicycle anywhere.

662
00:26:18,160 --> 00:26:19,000
 Where is it?

663
00:26:19,000 --> 00:26:21,000
 Oh, that's all right, Alice, has it?

664
00:26:21,000 --> 00:26:22,560
 Alice has it.

665
00:26:22,560 --> 00:26:23,680
 She's out delivering.

666
00:26:23,680 --> 00:26:25,440
 She's what?

667
00:26:25,440 --> 00:26:27,600
 Listen, Sam, have you bought this drug store?

668
00:26:27,600 --> 00:26:30,280
 Mr. McCall, Mr. McCall.

669
00:26:30,280 --> 00:26:32,920
 Oh, my Sam Ulrich.

670
00:26:32,920 --> 00:26:34,320
 Harriet, where did you come from?

671
00:26:34,320 --> 00:26:36,720
 Sam, I finally found 227 Maple Street.

672
00:26:36,720 --> 00:26:38,840
 But the lady says I can't have my 90 cents

673
00:26:38,840 --> 00:26:41,440
 until I get this bottle filled for them.

674
00:26:41,440 --> 00:26:42,280
 - What's it for?

675
00:26:42,280 --> 00:26:45,880
 - I don't know, but I've got a bridge game waiting.

676
00:26:45,880 --> 00:26:48,400
 - For just a minute, Harry.

677
00:26:48,400 --> 00:26:50,320
 Hello, McCall's pharmacy, good evening.

678
00:26:50,320 --> 00:26:51,720
 - Oh, Mr. McCall, this is Henry.

679
00:26:51,720 --> 00:26:52,560
 - This is who?

680
00:26:52,560 --> 00:26:55,680
 - Henry, all but remember, I've called up the Say I resign.

681
00:26:55,680 --> 00:26:57,680
 - Henry, this is your father.

682
00:26:57,680 --> 00:26:58,720
 - Is that your father?

683
00:26:58,720 --> 00:27:01,160
 He was how to get the wrong number, goodbye.

684
00:27:01,160 --> 00:27:02,960
 (audience laughing)

685
00:27:02,960 --> 00:27:04,520
 - Henry, Henry.

686
00:27:04,520 --> 00:27:06,920
 - What is that, Mike, last in chocolate?

687
00:27:06,920 --> 00:27:09,220
 Just a minute, lady. I'll be right with you.

688
00:27:09,220 --> 00:27:11,620
 Here, we'll get behind the counter here and give me a hand.

689
00:27:11,620 --> 00:27:12,620
 Who? What?

690
00:27:12,620 --> 00:27:13,620
 Mr. McCall.

691
00:27:13,620 --> 00:27:14,620
 Mr. McCall.

692
00:27:14,620 --> 00:27:15,620
 Is that you, Alice?

693
00:27:15,620 --> 00:27:16,620
 What?

694
00:27:16,620 --> 00:27:17,620
 Sam Paul, Richard.

695
00:27:17,620 --> 00:27:20,120
 How did you have to leave the house in the dirty apron?

696
00:27:20,120 --> 00:27:25,020
 You want me to get chocolate all over my suit?

697
00:27:25,020 --> 00:27:27,320
 Dear, if you've got a dollar for me because if you have,

698
00:27:27,320 --> 00:27:30,020
 give it to Mr. McCall right away because I'm quitting.

699
00:27:30,020 --> 00:27:31,020
 You're what?

700
00:27:31,020 --> 00:27:34,420
 Hello, McCall's pharmacy. Good evening.

701
00:27:34,420 --> 00:27:35,420
 Is this McCall?

702
00:27:35,420 --> 00:27:36,420
 It is.

703
00:27:36,420 --> 00:27:40,020
 - Mr. McCall. - Henry, don't you know your own father when he speaks to you?

704
00:27:40,020 --> 00:27:43,020
 Listen, Father. I thought you said this was McCall.

705
00:27:43,020 --> 00:27:45,420
 How do I keep getting the wrong number? Goodbye.

706
00:27:45,420 --> 00:27:48,020
 Henry! Wait!

707
00:27:48,020 --> 00:27:49,420
 Yes, Father, do you want me?

708
00:27:49,420 --> 00:27:51,020
 Why are you quitting your job down here?

709
00:27:51,020 --> 00:27:52,820
 Because I've got a swell one with Mr. Scott.

710
00:27:52,820 --> 00:27:55,820
 - Doing what? - Oh, it's nice outdoor work mixing cement.

711
00:27:55,820 --> 00:27:57,620
 Don't you think mother would want me to thank you?

712
00:27:57,620 --> 00:28:00,820
 Henry, you're not getting your mother mixed up in any cement.

